{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":71,"text":"Have you ever asked yourselves why it is that"},{"time":3117,"text":"companies, the really cool companies,"},{"time":5197,"text":"the innovative ones, the creative,"},{"time":6709,"text":"new economy-type companies --"},{"time":8511,"text":"Apple, Google, Facebook --"},{"time":11885,"text":"are coming out of one particular country,"},{"time":14573,"text":"the United States of America?"},{"time":16304,"text":"Usually when I say this, someone says, \"Spotify!"},{"time":18262,"text":"That's Europe.\" But, yeah."},{"time":19740,"text":"It has not had the impact that these other companies have had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23424,"text":"Now what I do is I'm an economist,"},{"time":25392,"text":"and I actually study the relationship"},{"time":26880,"text":"between innovation and economic growth"},{"time":28925,"text":"at the level of the company, the industry and the nation,"},{"time":31824,"text":"and I work with policymakers worldwide,"},{"time":33939,"text":"especially in the European Commission,"},{"time":35410,"text":"but recently also in interesting places like China,"},{"time":38721,"text":"and I can tell you that that question"},{"time":40596,"text":"is on the tip of all of their tongues:"},{"time":43196,"text":"Where are the European Googles?"},{"time":45415,"text":"What is the secret behind the Silicon Valley growth model,"},{"time":49160,"text":"which they understand is different"},{"time":51168,"text":"from this old economy growth model?"},{"time":54049,"text":"And what is interesting is that often,"},{"time":56728,"text":"even if we're in the 21st century,"},{"time":58307,"text":"we kind of come down in the end to these ideas"},{"time":60690,"text":"of market versus state."},{"time":62663,"text":"It's talked about in these modern ways,"},{"time":64715,"text":"but the idea is that somehow, behind places like Silicon Valley,"},{"time":68478,"text":"the secret have been different types of market-making mechanisms,"},{"time":72264,"text":"the private initiative, whether this be about"},{"time":75536,"text":"a dynamic venture capital sector"},{"time":77750,"text":"that's actually able to provide that high-risk finance"},{"time":80096,"text":"to these innovative companies,"},{"time":81769,"text":"the gazelles as we often call them,"},{"time":83894,"text":"which traditional banks are scared of,"},{"time":85889,"text":"or different types of really successful"},{"time":87921,"text":"commercialization policies which actually allow these companies"},{"time":90927,"text":"to bring these great inventions, their products,"},{"time":93182,"text":"to the market and actually get over this"},{"time":95205,"text":"really scary Death Valley period"},{"time":97456,"text":"in which many companies instead fail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100022,"text":"But what really interests me, especially nowadays"},{"time":102798,"text":"and because of what's happening politically around the world,"},{"time":105759,"text":"is the language that's used, the narrative,"},{"time":109012,"text":"the discourse, the images, the actual words."},{"time":112171,"text":"So we often are presented"},{"time":114476,"text":"with the kind of words like that the private sector"},{"time":117449,"text":"is also much more innovative because it's able to"},{"time":119719,"text":"think out of the box."},{"time":121319,"text":"They are more dynamic."},{"time":123572,"text":"Think of Steve Jobs' really inspirational speech"},{"time":126326,"text":"to the 2005 graduating class at Stanford,"},{"time":129464,"text":"where he said to be innovative,"},{"time":131556,"text":"you've got to stay hungry, stay foolish."},{"time":134326,"text":"Right? So these guys are kind of the hungry"},{"time":135861,"text":"and foolish and colorful guys, right?"},{"time":138012,"text":"And in places like Europe,"},{"time":139965,"text":"it might be more equitable,"},{"time":141550,"text":"we might even be a bit better dressed"},{"time":143112,"text":"and eat better than the U.S.,"},{"time":145378,"text":"but the problem is this damn public sector."},{"time":149410,"text":"It's a bit too big, and it hasn't actually allowed"},{"time":153403,"text":"these things like dynamic venture capital"},{"time":156168,"text":"and commercialization to actually be able to really"},{"time":158902,"text":"be as fruitful as it could."},{"time":160606,"text":"And even really respectable newspapers,"},{"time":162558,"text":"some that I'm actually subscribed to,"},{"time":164645,"text":"the words they use are, you know,"},{"time":166598,"text":"the state as this Leviathan. Right?"},{"time":169701,"text":"This monster with big tentacles."},{"time":171834,"text":"They're very explicit in these editorials."},{"time":173738,"text":"They say, \"You know, the state, it's necessary"},{"time":176267,"text":"to fix these little market failures"},{"time":178193,"text":"when you have public goods"},{"time":179952,"text":"or different types of negative externalities like pollution,"},{"time":182784,"text":"but you know what, what is the next big revolution"},{"time":185839,"text":"going to be after the Internet?"},{"time":187257,"text":"We all hope it might be something green,"},{"time":189191,"text":"or all of this nanotech stuff, and in order for that stuff to happen,\" they say --"},{"time":193400,"text":"this was a special issue on the next industrial revolution --"},{"time":196266,"text":"they say, \"the state, just stick to the basics, right?"},{"time":198921,"text":"Fund the infrastructure. Fund the schools."},{"time":201409,"text":"Even fund the basic research, because this is"},{"time":203432,"text":"popularly recognized, in fact, as a big public good"},{"time":206101,"text":"which private companies don't want to invest in,"},{"time":208259,"text":"do that, but you know what?"},{"time":209820,"text":"Leave the rest to the revolutionaries.\""},{"time":212600,"text":"Those colorful, out-of-the-box kind of thinkers."},{"time":215897,"text":"They're often called garage tinkerers,"},{"time":217524,"text":"because some of them actually did some things in garages,"},{"time":219554,"text":"even though that's partly a myth."},{"time":222129,"text":"And so what I want to do with you in, oh God,"},{"time":224423,"text":"only 10 minutes,"},{"time":225607,"text":"is to really think again this juxtaposition,"},{"time":228597,"text":"because it actually has massive, massive implications"},{"time":231456,"text":"beyond innovation policy,"},{"time":232950,"text":"which just happens to be the area"},{"time":234710,"text":"that I often talk with with policymakers."},{"time":237590,"text":"It has huge implications, even with this whole notion"},{"time":241308,"text":"that we have on where, when and why"},{"time":244508,"text":"we should actually be cutting back on public spending"},{"time":247581,"text":"and different types of public services which,"},{"time":249626,"text":"of course, as we know, are increasingly being"},{"time":251383,"text":"outsourced because of this juxtaposition."},{"time":253445,"text":"Right? I mean, the reason that we need to maybe have free schools or charter schools"},{"time":256908,"text":"is in order to make them more innovative without being emburdened"},{"time":260770,"text":"by this heavy hand of the state curriculum, or something."},{"time":263521,"text":"So these kind of words are constantly,"},{"time":265504,"text":"these juxtapositions come up everywhere,"},{"time":267368,"text":"not just with innovation policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270216,"text":"And so to think again,"},{"time":271887,"text":"there's no reason that you should believe me,"},{"time":274293,"text":"so just think of some of the smartest"},{"time":275755,"text":"revolutionary things that you have in your pockets"},{"time":278026,"text":"and do not turn it on, but you might want to take it out, your iPhone."},{"time":280968,"text":"Ask who actually funded the really cool,"},{"time":283614,"text":"revolutionary thinking-out-of-the-box"},{"time":285746,"text":"things in the iPhone."},{"time":287533,"text":"What actually makes your phone"},{"time":289276,"text":"a smartphone, basically, instead of a stupid phone?"},{"time":291195,"text":"So the Internet, which you can surf the web"},{"time":293286,"text":"anywhere you are in the world;"},{"time":294994,"text":"GPS, where you can actually know where you are"},{"time":297578,"text":"anywhere in the world;"},{"time":298911,"text":"the touchscreen display, which makes it also"},{"time":301044,"text":"a really easy-to-use phone for anybody."},{"time":303509,"text":"These are the very smart, revolutionary bits about the iPhone,"},{"time":307226,"text":"and they're all government-funded."},{"time":311627,"text":"And the point is that the Internet"},{"time":314216,"text":"was funded by DARPA, U.S. Department of Defense."},{"time":316460,"text":"GPS was funded by the military's Navstar program."},{"time":320355,"text":"Even Siri was actually funded by DARPA."},{"time":323113,"text":"The touchscreen display was funded"},{"time":325052,"text":"by two public grants by the CIA and the NSF"},{"time":329847,"text":"to two public university researchers at the University of Delaware."},{"time":334302,"text":"Now, you might be thinking, \"Well, she's just said"},{"time":336520,"text":"the word 'defense' and 'military' an awful lot,\""},{"time":338855,"text":"but what's really interesting is that this is actually true"},{"time":341107,"text":"in sector after sector and department after department."},{"time":344115,"text":"So the pharmaceutical industry, which I am personally"},{"time":346253,"text":"very interested in because I've actually had the fortune"},{"time":348182,"text":"to study it in quite some depth,"},{"time":350896,"text":"is wonderful to be asking this question"},{"time":353073,"text":"about the revolutionary versus non-revolutionary bits,"},{"time":355820,"text":"because each and every medicine can actually be"},{"time":357836,"text":"divided up on whether it really is revolutionary or incremental."},{"time":361807,"text":"So the new molecular entities with priority rating"},{"time":364580,"text":"are the revolutionary new drugs,"},{"time":366855,"text":"whereas the slight variations of existing drugs --"},{"time":369756,"text":"Viagra, different color, different dosage --"},{"time":371747,"text":"are the less revolutionary ones."},{"time":374040,"text":"And it turns out that a full 75 percent"},{"time":376897,"text":"of the new molecular entities with priority rating"},{"time":379674,"text":"are actually funded in boring, Kafka-ian public sector labs."},{"time":384785,"text":"This doesn't mean that Big Pharma is not spending on innovation."},{"time":387468,"text":"They do. They spend on the marketing part."},{"time":389519,"text":"They spend on the D part of R&amp;D."},{"time":391667,"text":"They spend an awful lot on buying back their stock,"},{"time":394214,"text":"which is quite problematic."},{"time":396115,"text":"In fact, companies like Pfizer and Amgen recently"},{"time":398332,"text":"have spent more money in buying back their shares"},{"time":400923,"text":"to boost their stock price than on R&amp;D,"},{"time":402959,"text":"but that's a whole different TED Talk which one day"},{"time":405287,"text":"I'd be fascinated to tell you about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408551,"text":"Now, what's interesting in all of this"},{"time":410554,"text":"is the state, in all these examples,"},{"time":412788,"text":"was doing so much more than just fixing market failures."},{"time":416902,"text":"It was actually shaping and creating markets."},{"time":419631,"text":"It was funding not only the basic research,"},{"time":421907,"text":"which again is a typical public good,"},{"time":424266,"text":"but even the applied research."},{"time":425858,"text":"It was even, God forbid, being a venture capitalist."},{"time":429534,"text":"So these SBIR and SDTR programs,"},{"time":432633,"text":"which give small companies early-stage finance"},{"time":436664,"text":"have not only been extremely important"},{"time":438879,"text":"compared to private venture capital,"},{"time":440976,"text":"but also have become increasingly important."},{"time":443993,"text":"Why? Because, as many of us know,"},{"time":446869,"text":"V.C. is actually quite short-term."},{"time":448736,"text":"They want their returns in three to five years."},{"time":450525,"text":"Innovation takes a much longer time than that,"},{"time":453054,"text":"15 to 20 years."},{"time":454881,"text":"And so this whole notion -- I mean, this is the point, right?"},{"time":457268,"text":"Who's actually funding the hard stuff?"},{"time":459595,"text":"Of course, it's not just the state."},{"time":461320,"text":"The private sector does a lot."},{"time":462550,"text":"But the narrative that we've always been told"},{"time":464749,"text":"is the state is important for the basics,"},{"time":467632,"text":"but not really providing that sort of high-risk,"},{"time":469912,"text":"revolutionary thinking out of the box."},{"time":472212,"text":"In all these sectors, from funding the Internet"},{"time":474544,"text":"to doing the spending, but also the envisioning,"},{"time":477449,"text":"the strategic vision, for these investments,"},{"time":479740,"text":"it was actually coming within the state."},{"time":481328,"text":"The nanotechnology sector is actually fascinating"},{"time":483697,"text":"to study this, because the word itself, nanotechnology,"},{"time":486795,"text":"came from within government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488766,"text":"And so there's huge implications of this."},{"time":491113,"text":"First of all, of course I'm not someone,"},{"time":493218,"text":"this old-fashioned person, market versus state."},{"time":495220,"text":"What we all know in dynamic capitalism"},{"time":497745,"text":"is that what we actually need are public-private partnerships."},{"time":500804,"text":"But the point is, by constantly depicting"},{"time":503543,"text":"the state part as necessary"},{"time":505668,"text":"but actually -- pffff -- a bit boring"},{"time":508549,"text":"and often a bit dangerous kind of Leviathan,"},{"time":511598,"text":"I think we've actually really stunted the possibility"},{"time":514350,"text":"to build these public-private partnerships"},{"time":515922,"text":"in a really dynamic way."},{"time":517468,"text":"Even the words that we often use to justify the \"P\" part,"},{"time":520662,"text":"the public part -- well, they're both P's --"},{"time":522890,"text":"with public-private partnerships"},{"time":524250,"text":"is in terms of de-risking."},{"time":526305,"text":"What the public sector did in all these examples"},{"time":528766,"text":"I just gave you, and there's many more,"},{"time":530853,"text":"which myself and other colleagues have been looking at,"},{"time":534317,"text":"is doing much more than de-risking."},{"time":535867,"text":"It's kind of been taking on that risk. Bring it on."},{"time":538433,"text":"It's actually been the one thinking out of the box."},{"time":541006,"text":"But also, I'm sure you all have had experience"},{"time":543717,"text":"with local, regional, national governments,"},{"time":545777,"text":"and you're kind of like, \"You know what, that Kafka-ian bureaucrat, I've met him.\""},{"time":548924,"text":"That whole juxtaposition thing, it's kind of there."},{"time":552368,"text":"Well, there's a self-fulfilling prophecy."},{"time":554182,"text":"By talking about the state as kind of irrelevant,"},{"time":556348,"text":"boring, it's sometimes"},{"time":558675,"text":"that we actually create those organizations in that way."},{"time":560887,"text":"So what we have to actually do is build"},{"time":563088,"text":"these entrepreneurial state organizations."},{"time":565264,"text":"DARPA, that funded the Internet and Siri,"},{"time":567753,"text":"actually thought really hard about this,"},{"time":569338,"text":"how to welcome failure, because you will fail."},{"time":572031,"text":"You will fail when you innovative."},{"time":573956,"text":"One out of 10 experiments has any success."},{"time":577828,"text":"And the V.C. guys know this,"},{"time":579566,"text":"and they're able to actually fund the other losses"},{"time":581438,"text":"from that one success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583292,"text":"And this brings me, actually, probably,"},{"time":584785,"text":"to the biggest implication,"},{"time":587380,"text":"and this has huge implications beyond innovation."},{"time":590047,"text":"If the state is more than just a market fixer,"},{"time":593707,"text":"if it actually is a market shaper,"},{"time":595519,"text":"and in doing that has had to take on this massive risk,"},{"time":598487,"text":"what happened to the reward?"},{"time":600481,"text":"We all know, if you've ever taken a finance course,"},{"time":602855,"text":"the first thing you're taught is sort of the risk-reward relationship,"},{"time":606261,"text":"and so some people are foolish enough"},{"time":607881,"text":"or probably smart enough if they have time to wait,"},{"time":610343,"text":"to actually invest in stocks, because they're higher risk"},{"time":612825,"text":"which over time will make a greater reward than bonds,"},{"time":615345,"text":"that whole risk-reward thing."},{"time":616924,"text":"Well, where's the reward for the state"},{"time":618897,"text":"of having taken on these massive risks"},{"time":621353,"text":"and actually been foolish enough to have done the Internet?"},{"time":623812,"text":"The Internet was crazy."},{"time":625764,"text":"It really was. I mean, the probability of failure was massive."},{"time":628916,"text":"You had to be completely nuts to do it,"},{"time":631526,"text":"and luckily, they were."},{"time":633307,"text":"Now, we don't even get to this question about rewards"},{"time":635808,"text":"unless you actually depict the state as this risk-taker."},{"time":639956,"text":"And the problem is that economists often think,"},{"time":642557,"text":"well, there is a reward back to the state. It's tax."},{"time":645043,"text":"You know, the companies will pay tax,"},{"time":646592,"text":"the jobs they create will create growth"},{"time":648882,"text":"so people who get those jobs and their incomes rise"},{"time":652033,"text":"will come back to the state through the tax mechanism."},{"time":655257,"text":"Well, unfortunately, that's not true."},{"time":657247,"text":"Okay, it's not true because many of the jobs that are created go abroad."},{"time":660766,"text":"Globalization, and that's fine. We shouldn't be nationalistic."},{"time":663733,"text":"Let the jobs go where they have to go, perhaps."},{"time":665940,"text":"I mean, one can take a position on that."},{"time":668029,"text":"But also these companies"},{"time":669693,"text":"that have actually had this massive benefit from the state --"},{"time":672765,"text":"Apple's a great example."},{"time":674626,"text":"They even got the first -- well, not the first,"},{"time":676675,"text":"but 500,000 dollars actually went to Apple, the company,"},{"time":681243,"text":"through this SBIC program,"},{"time":683912,"text":"which predated the SBIR program,"},{"time":685960,"text":"as well as, as I said before, all the technologies behind the iPhone."},{"time":689278,"text":"And yet we know they legally,"},{"time":691768,"text":"as many other companies, pay very little tax back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695450,"text":"So what we really need to actually rethink"},{"time":698437,"text":"is should there perhaps be a return-generating mechanism"},{"time":702696,"text":"that's much more direct than tax. Why not?"},{"time":705383,"text":"It could happen perhaps through equity."},{"time":707953,"text":"This, by the way, in the countries"},{"time":709760,"text":"that are actually thinking about this strategically,"},{"time":712064,"text":"countries like Finland in Scandinavia,"},{"time":714195,"text":"but also in China and Brazil,"},{"time":716230,"text":"they're retaining equity in these investments."},{"time":718560,"text":"Sitra funded Nokia, kept equity, made a lot of money,"},{"time":722386,"text":"it's a public funding agency in Finland,"},{"time":725046,"text":"which then funded the next round of Nokias."},{"time":727872,"text":"The Brazilian Development Bank,"},{"time":729881,"text":"which is providing huge amounts of funds today"},{"time":732676,"text":"to clean technology, they just announced"},{"time":734473,"text":"a $56 billion program for the future on this,"},{"time":738722,"text":"is retaining equity in these investments."},{"time":742261,"text":"So to put it provocatively,"},{"time":743773,"text":"had the U.S. government thought about this,"},{"time":746712,"text":"and maybe just brought back"},{"time":748556,"text":"just something called an innovation fund,"},{"time":750981,"text":"you can bet that, you know, if even just .05 percent"},{"time":754113,"text":"of the profits from what the Internet produced"},{"time":755996,"text":"had come back to that innovation fund,"},{"time":757654,"text":"there would be so much more money"},{"time":759278,"text":"to spend today on green technology."},{"time":761506,"text":"Instead, many of the state budgets"},{"time":763000,"text":"which in theory are trying to do that"},{"time":765598,"text":"are being constrained."},{"time":767434,"text":"But perhaps even more important,"},{"time":769244,"text":"we heard before about the one percent,"},{"time":771111,"text":"the 99 percent."},{"time":772686,"text":"If the state is thought about in this more strategic way,"},{"time":776431,"text":"as one of the lead players in the value creation mechanism,"},{"time":779464,"text":"because that's what we're talking about, right?"},{"time":781285,"text":"Who are the different players in creating value"},{"time":783219,"text":"in the economy, and is the state's role,"},{"time":785514,"text":"has it been sort of dismissed as being a backseat player?"},{"time":789243,"text":"If we can actually have a broader theory"},{"time":791598,"text":"of value creation and allow us to actually admit"},{"time":793651,"text":"what the state has been doing and reap something back,"},{"time":796702,"text":"it might just be that in the next round,"},{"time":799521,"text":"and I hope that we all hope that the next big revolution"},{"time":802087,"text":"will in fact be green,"},{"time":803728,"text":"that that period of growth"},{"time":805451,"text":"will not only be smart, innovation-led,"},{"time":808141,"text":"not only green, but also more inclusive,"},{"time":811327,"text":"so that the public schools in places like Silicon Valley"},{"time":814581,"text":"can actually also benefit from that growth,"},{"time":817321,"text":"because they have not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":818920,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820173,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}